**Features:** `recursion`, `strong-induction`, `recursive-equation-unfold`, `slice-indexing`, `vec-output-construction`, `extend-from-slice-step`, `usize-add-no-overflow`, `bv-nat-bridge`, `usize-beq-zero-bridge`, `shared-aux-lemma`, `bundled-postcondition-projection`, `ok-result-implies-no-overflow`, `mixed-chunk-size-extend` (new), `parity-split-output-invariant` (new), `branch-dependent-step-lemma` (new), `interleaved-output-construction` (new), `truncated-subtraction-length-spec` (new), `first-iteration-special-case`, `elementwise-output-invariant`.

**Summary (one line):** Tail-recursive interspersing scan with branch-dependent typed chunk sizes ([i64;1] on the first element, [i64;2] on delimiter+element) and dual parity-split output invariants (even slots = source, odd slots = delimiter) under truncated-subtraction length `2nтИТ1`, with the size-2 branch's capacity precondition recovered by `ok-result-implies-no-overflow` against the extend_from_slice fail path.

**Why a new entry over `clever_009_rolling_max_modified`:** rolling_max pushes a single 1-element chunk per step with a single elementwise invariant; the new pattern adds three structurally distinct obstacles тАФ (1) two different chunk sizes in the same function requiring paired `push_one`/`push_two` + paired step lemmas + two `extend_from_slice` unfoldings, (2) lockstep parity-split invariants where the per-step preservation must case on whether the new index lands in the even (source) or odd (delimiter) slot, and (3) the `ok-result-implies-no-overflow` discharge of the size-2 path's `acc.val.size + 2 < USize64.size` against the `maximumSizeExceeded` fail bind тАФ a Vec-capacity application of an idiom previously only seen for arithmetic overflow (`below_zero`, `is_prime`).

**Note for human reader:** This is the first Vec-output proof in the library where the per-step append length varies by branch. The `getElem_congr_idx`-on-computed-offset technique to close the right-half of the append case-split (offset = 0 or 1 depending on parity and chunk size) is the transferable kernel for future patterns that interleave or zip into a Vec.

